Introduction

Dojun, formerly known as J and Jun is a South Korean singer and rapper.

Dojun made his first debut on April 10, 2020, when he was added as a member of the boy group EASTONE under TSN Company. The group presumably disbanded sometime in the same year.

The same year, he was revealed as a member of the pre-debut group ONE A DAY, which again presumably disbanded in either August or September of 2020.

On March 2, 2021, Dojun was announced as one of the two new members of DUSTIN under Na Entertainment. He probably left the group when they disbanded on May 24, 2021, as he wasn’t a part of the lineup when they reformed in December 2021.

Dojun was then revealed as a member of the pre-debut boy group Be on new under Be the max Entertainment. However, he left the company in December 2022 and never made his debut with them.

He then was announced as a member of the upcoming boy group (M)IRROR (formerly known as VT Trainee) under VT Entertainment, in which he debuted on May 12, 2023. Unfortunately, the group presumably disbanded due to their inactivity.
